!! Plugin files

|!File |!Role |
|`modules/widgets/scribe.js` |The `<$scribe>` widget itself |
|`modules/scribetypes/plain.js` |`text/plain` handler |
|`modules/scribetypes/json.js` |`application/json` handler |
|`modules/scribetypes/string-array.js` |`application/x-string-array` handler |
|`test/scribetypes.js` |Jasmine specs for handlers + the widget |

!! Restart rules

|!Change |!Restart? |
|Edit any `.js` (widget or handler) |Yes — JS modules require server restart |
|Add a new scribetype handler |Yes |
|Edit doc tiddlers / readme |No |

!! Adding a new type handler

Drop a new file under `modules/scribetypes/<mime>.js` exporting `name`, `fromField`, `toField`. After restart, it's discoverable by `<$scribe type="<your-mime>">`.

Example: a comma-separated-list handler

```js
exports.name = "application/x-csv-row";
exports.fromField = function(value) {
  if (!value) return "";
  return Array.isArray(value) ? value.join(", ") : String(value);
};
exports.toField = function(text) {
  return text ? text.split(/\s*,\s*/) : [];
};
```

!! Running tests

```
bin/tw test scribe
```

Tests cover each handler's fromField/toField and several `<$scribe>` widget scenarios (whole-field round-trip, sub-path scalar, sub-path string-array, clear-deletes-key, unknown-type fallback).

